(4059,	774,	'features',	'<ul>\r\n 	<li>Web platform (no software installation required on the user\'s PC)</li>\r\n 	<li>Access with institutional credentials</li>\r\n 	<li>Signature certificates already available on the platform (for authorized users)</li>\r\n 	<li>Ability to sign multiple documents at once</li>\r\n 	<li>Option to delegate signature to another signer (if registered in the system)</li>\r\n 	<li>Monitoring and archiving of the signing process and related files</li>\r\n 	<li>Integration with Titulus document management system</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(4062,	774,	'requirements',	'The university’s U-Sign platform is available only to authorized users, even if they do not have an active digital signature certificate (in “secretary” mode). If you encounter access issues, please contact the helpdesk.\r\n\r\n<strong>Notice for digital signature certificate holders</strong>\r\nThe digital signature certificate is issued to named individuals and involves a cost for the University. Please make sure to keep your PIN safe: losing it will result in the revocation of the certificate and require reissuance, generating additional costs for the University.'),
(4065,	774,	'get_started',	'<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong>Access the portal</strong>\r\nGo to the U-Sign website and log in with your institutional credentials (e.g., Single Sign-On, SPID, or CIE).</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Upload the document</strong>\r\nSelect or drag and drop the file to be signed (PDF). You may also import it from an integrated document management system.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Define the signers</strong>\r\nAdd the recipients to the signing workflow, choosing whether the signature should be sequential or parallel. You may also assign delegates or roles.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Set the type of signature</strong>\r\nChoose the required type of signature (CAdES, PAdES, graphic) based on the document type and applicable regulations.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Start the signing workflow</strong>\r\nSend the document: signers will receive a notification and can sign directly from the platform.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Download or archive</strong>\r\nOnce the process is complete, you can download the signed document or keep it stored in the system for compliant archiving.</li>\r\n</ol>'),
